  - id: 58
    questionText:
      en: Why do Polish people clap when the plane lands?
      native: "Dlaczego Polacy klaszcz\u0105 po wyl\u0105dowaniu?"
    questionVisual: {fileID: 2800000, guid: 5c0ae1f17a97b3646b13d59d46097485, type: 3}
    answer0:
      en: To thank the pilot
      native: "\u017Beby podzi\u0119kowa\u0107 pilotowi"
    answer0_Image: {fileID: 0}
    answer1:
      en: They are happy to be alive
      native: "Ciesz\u0105 si\u0119, \u017Ce prze\u017Cyli"
    answer1_Image: {fileID: 0}
    answer2:
      en: It is a rule
      native: Taka jest zasada
    answer2_Image: {fileID: 0}
    answer3:
      en: They saw a bird
      native: Zobaczyli ptaka
    answer3_Image: {fileID: 0}
    useQuestionAnswer: 1
    correctIndices: 00000000
    useImageAnswers: 0
  tiers:
  - title:
      en: Russian Spy
      native: Ruski Szpieg
    maxPercentage: 12
    subtitle:
      en: O kurwa...
      native: O kurwa...
    description:
      en: "You think Krak\xF3w is a type of cracker and you put ketchup on your Pierogi.
        The ABW has been notified of your location. Please remain seated."
      native: "My\u015Blisz, \u017Ce Krak\xF3w to rodzaj krakersa i polewasz pierogi
        keczupem. ABW zosta\u0142a powiadomiona o twojej lokalizacji. Prosz\u0119
        pozosta\u0107 na miejscu."
  - title:
      en: German Tourist
      native: Niemiecki Turysta
    maxPercentage: 25
    subtitle:
      en: Was ist das?
      native: Was ist das?
    description:
      en: You are just here for the cheap beer and the dentist. You think Pierogi
        is Polish Pasta and you are scared of the cashier at Biedronka.
      native: "Jeste\u015B tu tylko dla taniego piwa i dentysty. My\u015Blisz, \u017Ce
        pierogi to polski makaron i boisz si\u0119 kasjerki w Biedronce."
  - title:
      en: Erasmus Student
      native: Student Erasmusa
    maxPercentage: 40
    subtitle:
      en: Na Zdrowie!
      native: Na Zdrowie!
    description:
      en: You love Soplica Hazelnut vodka and you know how to say Kurwa. You think
        Zakopane is a hidden gem. You still smile at strangers on the street (stop
        doing that).
      native: "Kochasz Soplic\u0119 Orzechow\u0105 i znasz s\u0142owo Kurwa. My\u015Blisz,
        \u017Ce Zakopane to ukryty skarb. Wci\u0105\u017C u\u015Bmiechasz si\u0119
        do obcych na ulicy (przesta\u0144 to robi\u0107)."
  - title:
      en: Average Kowalski
      native: "Przeci\u0119tny Kowalski"
    maxPercentage: 60
    subtitle:
      en: It'll be fine somehow
      native: "Jako\u015B to b\u0119dzie"
    description:
      en: You complain about the weather, the government, and the neighbors. You
        have a plastic bag full of other plastic bags in your kitchen. You pay your
        taxes, but you do it with great sadness.
      native: "Narzekasz na pogod\u0119, rz\u0105d i s\u0105siad\xF3w. Masz w kuchni
        reklam\xF3wk\u0119 pe\u0142n\u0105 innych reklam\xF3wek. P\u0142acisz podatki,
        ale robisz to z wielkim smutkiem."
  - title:
      en: The Janusz - True Pole
      native: Janusz - Prawdziwy Polak
    maxPercentage: 75
    subtitle:
      en: Passat B5 Driver
      native: Kierowca Passata B5
    description:
      en: You own a tactical screen (parawan) for Baltic sea battles. You wear socks
        with sandals because it is aerodynamic. You know the price of butter in three
        different supermarkets.
      native: "Posiadasz taktyczny parawan do bitew morskich w Ba\u0142tyku. Nosisz
        skarpety do sanda\u0142\xF3w, bo to aerodynamiczne. Znasz cen\u0119 mas\u0142a
        w trzech r\xF3\u017Cnych supermarketach."
  - title:
      en: Babcia's Favorite
      native: Wnuczek Babci
    maxPercentage: 85
    subtitle:
      en: Eat the meat, leave the potatoes
      native: "Zjedz mi\u0119sko, ziemniaczki zostaw"
    description:
      en: "You are never hungry. You have an infinite supply of incomprehensible
        proverbs. You can spot a draft (przeci\u0105g) from three rooms away and
        you believe it is lethal."
      native: "Nigdy nie jeste\u015B g\u0142odny. Znasz niesko\u0144czon\u0105 liczb\u0119
        niezrozumia\u0142ych przys\u0142\xF3w. Wyczuwasz przeci\u0105g z trzech pokoi
        dalej i wiesz, \u017Ce jest \u015Bmiertelny."
  - title:
      en: Pope's Driver
      native: "Kierowca Papie\u017Ca"
    maxPercentage: 94
    subtitle:
      en: JP2GMD
      native: JP2GMD
    description:
      en: "You vibrate at the holy frequency of 21:37. You consume Cream Pies (Krem\xF3wki)
        for breakfast. Your blood type is Onion Juice."
      native: "Wibrujesz na \u015Bwi\u0119tej cz\u0119stotliwo\u015Bci 21:37. Jesz
        krem\xF3wki na \u015Bniadanie. Twoja grupa krwi to Sok z Cebuli."
  - title:
      en: Messiah of Nations
      native: "Mesjasz Narod\xF3w"
    maxPercentage: 100
    subtitle:
      en: Glory to Great Poland
      native: "Chwa\u0142a Wielkiej Polsce"
    description:
      en: You have transcended Poland; you are Poland. You have resurrected the Winged
        Hussars. Robert Lewandowski has a poster of you on his wall. You pay for
        the toilet at the train station... and you enjoy it.
      native: "Przekroczy\u0142e\u015B granice polsko\u015Bci; jeste\u015B Polsk\u0105.
        Wskrzesi\u0142e\u015B Husari\u0119. Robert Lewandowski ma tw\xF3j plakat
        na \u015Bcianie. P\u0142acisz za toalet\u0119 na dworcu... i sprawia ci to
        przyjemno\u015B\u0107."
